Package edu.usca.acsc492l.flightplanner

Class Summary
Airplane A model class that represents an Airplane object
Airport A class to define and construct airport objects.
Comm A model class to represent a Communication node in an Airport class
Coordinate A model class to represent the coordinate of either an Airport or NAVBeacon object
DatabaseModel A class to serve as a model for transferring data to and from an XML database
Destination A helper class to hold information regarding each destination in the flight plan.
Dijkstra Dijkstra's Shortest Path Algorithm for finding the shortest weighted path between two vertices (taken from Discrete Mathematics and Its Applications, 6th Edition, by Kenneth H.
Edge Holds a weighted edge between two Airport or NAVBeacon objects on a 2-dimensional plane
FlightPlan A class to generate a flight plan with input information from the user.
Main Serves as the main class of the application by providing a user interface through which the user may interact with the program.
NAVBeacon A model class that represents a NAV Beacon object
Runway A class to define and construct Runway objects.
Vertex Assists Dijkstra objects with determining the shortest path between any two Vertex nodes
 

Enum Summary
Airplane.AirplaneType Represents each available type of airplane
Comm.CommType Describes the various Airport frequencies
Edge.DirectionsEnum Holds the directions in which the Airplane may travel
NAVBeacon.NAVBeaconType Represents the various different types of NAV Beacons
Runway.RunwayType Represents the different types of Runways
 

Exception Summary
AirplaneException Thrown whenever an exception occurs in the Airplane class
AirportException Thrown when an Exception occurs in the Airport class
CommException Thrown when an Exception occurs in the Comm class
CoordinateException Thrown when an Exception occurs in the Coordinate class
DijkstraException Thrown whenever an exception occurs in the Dijkstra class
FlightPlanException Thrown whenever an exception occurs in the FlightPlan class
NAVBeaconException Thrown when an Exception occurs in the NAVBeacon class
RunwayException Thrown when an Exception occurs in the Runway class
VertexException Thrown whenever an exception occurs in the Vertex class
